Foyle's War - Series 1 - A Lesson In Murder/ Eagle Day/ The German Woman/ The White Feather
Foyle's War - Series 1 - A Lesson In Murder/ Eagle Day/ The German Woman/ The White Feather : short review
Boxset containing four episodes. May 1940 and World War Two rages over Europe. Michael Kitchen stars as Detective Chief Superintendent Christopher Foyle who feels that his skills would be better used aiding the war effort than fighting domestic crime in Sussex. His boss, Assistant Commissioner Summers, disagrees with him and sends him back to Hastings offering him help in the form of a cheerful driver Samantha Stewart. Includes The German Woman, The White Feather, A Lesson In Murder and Eagle Day.
