Agatha Christie - Miss Marple - Murder At The Vicarage
Geraldine McEwan takes on the role of world-famous crime writer Agatha Christie's shrewd and inquisitive Miss Jane Marple.
Miss Marple's sweet old lady exterior hides an excellent perception of human nature and a razor sharp intuition for solving crimes - murderers underestimate her at their peril!
When the vicar in Miss Marple's home village declares in exasperation that anyone who murdered Colonel Prothero would be doing the world a service, he does not realise his words will come back to haunt him.
The Colonel's death at the vicarage throws up a long list of potential murderers, as the unpopular local resident made many enemies.
